# Neo-brutalism frontend rule

- Use a centralized token layer for color, spacing, shadows, and typography before adding one-off styles.
- Keep styling in existing plain CSS architecture unless explicitly asked to migrate.
- Default visual language:
  - `#FFFDF5` canvas, `#000000` text/borders/shadows
  - accent colors `#FF6B6B`, `#FFD93D`, `#C4B5FD`
  - thick black borders (usually 4px) and hard offset shadows (no blur)
  - sharp corners by default (no medium rounding)
  - bold typography (700/900), uppercase for labels/actions
- Every interactive control must have mechanical interaction states:
  - hover lifts/snaps
  - active "press down" translation with reduced/removed shadow
  - clear keyboard focus-visible treatment
- Favor reusable classes/components over one-off rules; avoid duplicated CSS blocks.
- Avoid anti-patterns: soft gradients, blur/backdrop-blur, subtle gray palettes, low-contrast text.
- Preserve accessibility: semantic HTML, keyboard support, WCAG contrast, reduced motion support.
- Maintain responsive layouts mobile-first while keeping neo-brutalist character on all breakpoints.
